Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cryptosporidiosis, infection with _Cryptosporidium_ spp., is endemic in ruminants including sheep, cattle and goats. Transmission is seen in so called "petting farms" where children are close to animals, swimming pools (resistant to chlorination) and where surface water is used for drinking water. Animals may not be ill and thus quarantine is not a method to ensure the animals are not infected before the customers come in contact with them. - Mod.EP

